SUMMARY:BRAZIL — Deal Roadshow Call - Brazil
DESCRIPTION:Brazil represented by Daniel Cardoso Leal (National Treasury Secretary) and Helano Dias (Head of Public Debt Operations Department)\nIssuer: FEDERATIVE REPUBLIC OF BRAZIL (BRAZIL)\nRoadshow: DealRoadshow: https://dealroadshow.com | Entry Code: FROB2026 or https://dealroadshow.com/e/FROB2026\n\nDeal context:\nThe Federative Republic of Brazil (rated Ba1/BB/BB by Moody's/S&P/Fitch) has mandated BBVA\, BNP Paribas\, BofA Securities\, and UBS Investment Bank as Joint Bookrunners to arrange roadshow calls beginning April 14\, 2026\, ahead of a potential EUR-denominated benchmark-sized multi-tranche offering. The proposed transaction consists of three SEC-registered senior unsecured tranches: a 4-year (2030 Bonds)\, 7-year (2033 Bonds)\, and 10-year (2036 Bonds)\, subject to market conditions. BofA Securities is coordinating logistics\, with Brazil represented by National Treasury Secretary Daniel Cardoso Leal and Head of Public Debt Operations Helano Dias.
LOCATION:Conference Call
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR